metadata.name: Pinnacle
metadata.description:
I travelled over 20,000 km to photograph Kirkjufell mountain. Millions of years old, its layers were formed through volcanic eruptions and its unique shape was influenced by the pressure of two glaciers. It is both ancient and majestic.

This image was taken during a number of wintry nights of photography around Grundarfjörður, Iceland. My aim was to capture a unique perspective incorporating the many interesting elements presented here.

This is the first piece from my genesis collection.

Edition: 1/1
Title: Pinnacle
Artist: Tomas Milan
Dimensions: 5760 x 3840 px
Collection: Inspired by Nature
